{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Variant","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can retrieve the type of a variant from the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant\/gtype-swift.property","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Variant takes up only 20 bytes and can store almost any engine datatype"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"inside of it. Variants are rarely used to hold information for long periods of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"time. Instead, they are used mainly for communication, editing, serialization and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"moving data around."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Variant:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Can store almost any Godot engine datatype.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can perform operations between many variants. GDScript uses Variant as its atomic\/native datatype."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can be hashed, so it can be compared to other variants."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Can be used to convert safely between datatypes.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Can be used to abstract calling methods and their arguments. Godot exports all its functions through variants.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can be used to defer calls or move data between threads."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Can be serialized as binary and stored to disk, or transferred via network.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Can be serialized to text and use it for printing values and editable settings.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Can work as an exported property, so the editor can edit it universally.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Can be used for dictionaries, arrays, parsers, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Containers (","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GDictionary","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"): Both are implemented using variants."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GDictionary","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can match any datatype used as key to any other datatype.  An "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"just holds an array of Variants.  A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant"},{"type":"text","text":" can also hold a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GDictionary"},{"type":"text","text":" and an "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GArray"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inside."}]